column1: [{"classname": "airplane", "wiki": "A powered heavier-than-air aircraft with fixed wings."}, {"classname": "automobile", "wiki": "A type of vehicle designed to move on the ground under its own stored power and intended to carry a driver, a small number of additional passengers, and a very limited amount of other load. A car or motorcar."}, {"classname": "bird", "wiki": "A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, having a beaked mouth, and laying eggs."}, {"classname": "cat", "wiki": "An animal of the family Felidae:\n Synonym: felid"}, {"classname": "deer", "wiki": "A ruminant mammal with antlers and hooves of the family Cervidae, or one of several similar animals from related families of the order Artiodactyla."}, {"classname": "dog", "wiki": "A mammal, Canis familiaris or Canis lupus familiaris, that has been domesticated for thousands of years, of highly variable appearance due to human breeding."}, {"classname": "frog", "wiki": "A small tailless amphibian of the order Anura that typically hops."}, {"classname": "horse", "wiki": "Any of several animals related to Equus ferus caballus."}, {"classname": "ship", "wiki": "A water-borne vessel generally larger than a boat."}, {"classname": "truck", "wiki": "A small wheel or roller, specifically the wheel of a gun carriage."}]
